This paper deals with formalisms for temporal and spatial reasoning, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The use of Constraint Satisfaction Problems (CSPs) also suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the study of Block Algebra and Rectangle Algebra involves geometric concepts, which could place the paper in the computer graphics (cs.CG) sub-category.
